**#  Secure Messaging System with Cryptography (ECDH, HKDF, AES-GCM)**

A Python-based project that combines a chatbot interface with a secure messaging system and classical encryption methods.

This project blends interactive functionality with real-world cryptographic concepts, including secure key exchange and authenticated encryption.

Features
Chatbot
Simple interactive chatbot
Responds to basic inputs such as:
greetings
"how are you"
"your name"
Encryption Menu

Users can:

Encrypt and decrypt messages
Choose from:
Caesar Cipher
Affine Cipher
Reverse Cipher
Secure messaging demo (ECDH + AES-GCM)
Cryptography Concepts
Classical Encryption
Caesar Cipher
Affine Cipher
Reverse Cipher
Modern Cryptography
Elliptic Curve Diffie-Hellman (ECDH)
Enables secure key exchange between two parties
Allows both sides to derive a shared secret without transmitting it
HKDF (HMAC-based Key Derivation Function)
Converts the shared secret into a strong symmetric encryption key
AES-GCM Encryption
Provides:
Confidentiality (keeps data private)
Integrity (detects tampering)
Uses a unique nonce for each encryption
Secure Communication Demo

This project demonstrates a secure communication process:

Alice and Bob generate elliptic curve key pairs
Public keys are exchanged
A shared secret is derived using ECDH
HKDF derives a symmetric AES key
Messages are encrypted using AES-GCM

This mirrors the fundamental principles behind secure communication protocols such as HTTPS/TLS.

Technologies Used
Python
cryptography library
Elliptic Curve Cryptography (ECC)
AES-GCM
HKDF
How to Run
1. Install dependencies
pip install cryptography

Run the Program
python3 chatbot.py

Example Usage
Shared keys match: True

Alice: hello
Encrypted: 9f8a...
Bob receives: hello

